{"type":"message","id":"6098b95b","parentId":"fa714e0a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:54:08.097Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xfix4juvb32u_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 154814\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE (architecture analysis + integration spec)\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment done - key finding is that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts, not useful\r\n3. Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring (Strategy C)\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Need to test if this distinguishes \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clear: run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment. I need to:\r\n1. Create a new analysis script or modify the existing one to test this hybrid formula\r\n2. Run it on the 200 pulses\r\n3. Compare results against the binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60)\r\n\r\nLooking at the CFI compression synthesis doc, they had three strategies:\r\n- Strategy A: CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 (too aggressive)\r\n- Strategy B: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n- Strategy C (proposed): score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI should implement Strategy C and compare it against Strategy A and B.\r\n\r\nLet me write a Python script to do this experiment, run it, and then append results to the synthesis document.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified that constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are metaprogramming artifacts, but the proposed three-dimensional filter (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) is still a binary threshold approach. The hybrid score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) formula was proposed but not tested.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and run a Python experiment script to test the hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring approach (Strategy C) against the binary threshold strategies (A and B), comparing precision/recall on the labeled pulse dataset.\r\n```\r\n(old_text: (new file))\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nStrategy C Experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 Scoring\r\nCompares: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, sqrt(freq(T)/120))\r\nagainst binary threshold strategies A and B.\r\n\r\nHypothesis: Hybrid scoring better distinguishes:\r\n  - \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1.00) → low score due to sqrt penalty\r\n  - \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → high score\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data\r\npulse_dir = Path(\"state/pulses\")\r\npulses = sorted(pulse_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.json\"))[:200]  # Same 200 pulses\r\n\r\n# Load ground truth labels (from CFI compression synthesis)\r\nlabels_file = Path(\"research/cfi_labels.json\")\r\nif labels_file.exists():\r\n    with open(labels_file) as f:\r\n        labels = json.load(f)\r\nelse:\r\n    # Build from synthesis doc if not separate\r\n    labels = {}\r\n\r\n# Compute CFI and freq for each token\r\ntoken_stats = defaultdict(lambda: {\"cfi_sum\": 0.0, \"cfi_count\": 0, \"freq\": 0})\r\n\r\nfor pulse_file in pulses:\r\n    with open(pulse_file) as f:\r\n        pulse = json.load(f)\r\n    \r\n    tokens = pulse.get(\"tokens\", [])\r\n    for i, token in enumerate(tokens):\r\n        token_stats[token][\"freq\"] += 1\r\n        # CFI: appears in this pulse?\r\n        token_stats[token][\"cfi_sum\"] += 1.0\r\n        token_stats[token][\"cfi_count\"] += 1\r\n\r\n# Compute CFI for each token\r\nfor token, stats in token_stats.items():\r\n    stats[\"cfi\"] = stats[\"cfi_sum\"] / stats[\"cfi_count\"] if stats[\"cfi_count\"] > 0 else 0\r\n\r\n# Hybrid scoring: score = CFI × sqrt(freq/120)\r\ndef hybrid_score(token):\r\n    stats = token_stats[token]\r\n    cfi = stats[\"cfi\"]\r\n    freq = stats[\"freq\"]\r\n    freq_norm = min(1.0, (freq / 120) ** 0.5)  # sqrt to soften high freq\r\n    return cfi * freq_norm\r\n\r\n# Strategy thresholds\r\nSTRATEGIES = {\r\n    \"A (CFI≥0.7, freq<60)\": lambda t: token_stats[t][\"cfi\"] >= 0.7 and token_stats[t][\"freq\"] < 60,\r\n    \"B (CFI≥0.5, freq∈[3,120))\": lambda t: token_stats[t][\"cfi\"] >= 0.5 and 3 <= token_stats[t][\"freq\"] < 120,\r\n    \"C (hybrid score≥0.3)\": lambda t: hybrid_score(t) >= 0.3,\r\n    \"C (hybrid score≥0.4)\": lambda t: hybrid_score(t) >= 0.4,\r\n    \"C (hybrid score≥0.5)\": lambda t: hybrid_score(t) >= 0.5,\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Analyze each strategy\r\nresults = {}\r\nfor name, predicate in STRATEGIES.items():\r\n    selected = [t for t in token_stats if predicate(t)]\r\n    results[name] = {\r\n        \"count\": len(selected),\r\n        \"tokens\": selected[:20]  # Sample\r\n    }\r\n\r\n# Print summary\r\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\r\nprint(\"STRATEGY C EXPERIMENT RESULTS\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:48:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382048095}}
