{"type":"message","id":"e48759a9","parentId":"ce60f557","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:54:14.171Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gqckdko7o964_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName                      [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----                      [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154814.md 3/24/2026 3:48:36 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154717.md 3/24/2026 3:47:38 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154519.md 3/24/2026 3:45:42 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154320.md 3/24/2026 3:43:40 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154221.md 3/24/2026 3:42:42 PM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":698,"aggregated":"[32;1mName                      [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----                      [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154814.md 3/24/2026 3:48:36 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154717.md 3/24/2026 3:47:38 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154519.md 3/24/2026 3:45:42 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154320.md 3/24/2026 3:43:40 PM\r\npulse_2026-03-24 154221.md 3/24/2026 3:42:42 PM","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382054168}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b4d6f9e","parentId":"e48759a9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:54:20.395Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran, but it seems the log file wasn't updated yet. Maybe the pulse didn't complete yet. The script might have taken longer than expected. Let me check the pulse.ps1 to understand what it does, and also check if there's a running process. But wait - the exec command returned output. That output appears to be the content of a log file from 3:48 PM (154814), not from the 3:53 PM run.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the output: the exec result shows the content of the pulse log file `pulse_2026-03-24 154814.md`. The timestamp matches. But the cron triggered at 3:53 PM and the log shows 15:48. \n\nI think the cron job ran at 15:50 (based on the \"10min\" interval), and the script just logged what the next action should be rather than actually executing it. Let me re-read the pulse script to see what it's actually doing.","thinkingSignature":"00d0cc0076f94ed2f43f94306bd3c4ef7f86d10261bbd6524100c24feeefb374"},{"type":"text","text":"The pulse seems to have completed but the log only shows the observation/action, not a new run. Let me check the script and current state.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ojfuvn17piy3_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3521,"output":273,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16039,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382054172}}
{"type":"message","id":"f9c9fa46","parentId":"0b4d6f9e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:54:20.400Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ojfuvn17piy3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files -> apply pending mutations -> reason -> propose mutations -> log -> exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n    [switch]$AutoAccept = $false   # auto-apply ALL proposed mutations without prompting\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmmss\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read core files\n$goalsFile   = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$stanceFile  = \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\"\n$stance      = if (Test-Path $stanceFile) { Get-Content $stanceFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$goals       = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file.\" }\n$pending     = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Recent pulse\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n# Mutation dirs\n$proposedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\proposed\"\n$appliedDir   = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\applied\"\n$rejectedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\rejected\"\n\n# Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\n$appliedMutations   = @()\n$rejectedMutations   = @()\n\nif (Test-Path $proposedDir) {\n    foreach ($mfile in (Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" | Sort Name)) {\n        $lines   = Get-Content $mfile.FullName\n        $file    = $lines[0]\n        $oldText = ($lines[1] -replace '^---', '').Trim()\n        $newText = ($lines[2..($lines.Count-1)] -join \"`n\").Trim()\n\n        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $file\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            # New file case\n            if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n                $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                Write-Host \"[mutation applied] NEW FILE: $file\"\n                $appliedMutations += \"$file (new)\"\n                continue\n            }\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (missing)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # File exists — [NEW_FILE] on an existing file means REPLACE content (with newText)\n        if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n            if (-not $newText) {\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                $rejectedMutations += \"$file (empty [NEW_FILE] mutation)\"\n                Write-Host \"[mutation rejected] $file (empty [NEW_FILE])\"\n                continue\n            }\n            $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] REPLACED $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (replaced)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current.Length -eq 0 -or $current -notmatch [regex]::Escape($oldText)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (old text not found)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # Empty old_text but not [NEW_FILE] means APPEND to file\n        if (-not $oldText) {\n            $updated = $current + \"`n\" + $newText\n            $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] APPENDED to $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (appended)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $updated = $current.Replace($oldText, $newText)\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $file\"\n        $appliedMutations += $file\n    }\n}\n\n# Re-read files post-mutation\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# Sanitize text — replace curly quotes and em-dashes with ASCII equivalents for LLM compatibility\nfunction Normalize-Text($t) {\n    if (-not $t) { return \"\" }\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\"   # right single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\"   # left single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201C, '\"'   # left double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201D, '\"'   # right double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2014, '-'  # em dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2013, '-'  # en dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x03BB, \"λ\"  # Greek lambda — keep as-is but ensure UTF8\n    return $t\n}\n\n# LLM call\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n# Write prompt to file (Python handles UTF-8 cleanly, avoiding PS heredoc issues)\n$promptFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_prompt.txt\"\n$normalizedGoals = Normalize-Text $goals\n$normalizedPending = Normalize-Text $pending\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$promptText = \"You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$normalizedGoals\n\nPending:\n$normalizedPending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\nUse TRIPLE backticks (```) around the mutation block, NOT single backticks.\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or (new file) if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"\n\n$promptText | Out-File -FilePath $promptFile -Encoding UTF8 -NoNewline\n\n$llmPy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"call_llm.py\"\n$pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\nif (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n$psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n$psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n$psi.Arguments = \"`\"$llmPy`\" `\"$promptFile`\"\"\n$psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n$psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n$psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n$psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n$psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n$proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n$stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n$stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n$proc.WaitForExit()\n\n# Read response from file (written by Python, avoids console encoding issues)\n$responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 500  # give Python time to write\nif (Test-Path $responseFile) {\n    $llmResponse = Get-Content $responseFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] response length: $($llmResponse.Length)\"\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[LLM error: no response file]\"\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] no response file found\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block — use Python for robust field extraction\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$oldLine = \"\"; $newText = \"\"; $fileLine = \"\"\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\n    $parsePy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"parse_mutation.py\"\n    $pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\n    if (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n\n    $psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n    $psi.Arguments = \"`\"$parsePy`\" `\"$responseFile`\"\"\n    $psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n    $psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n    $psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n    $psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n    $psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n    $proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n    $stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n    $stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n    $proc.WaitForExit()\n\n    # Read parsed result from JSON file\n    $resultFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".mutation_parse_result.json\"\n    if (Test-Path $resultFile) {\n        try {\n            $parseResult = Get-Content $resultFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8 | ConvertFrom-Json\n            $oldLine = $parseResult.old\n            $newText = $parseResult.new\n            $fileLine = $parseResult.file\n            Write-Host \"[mutation parsed via Python] old='$($oldLine.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(30, $oldLine.Length)))' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n        } catch {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation JSON parse error] $_\"\n        }\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed via Python] stderr: $stderr\"\n    }\n\n    # Fallback: infer file from ACTION block if not found\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:`([^`]+)`|([^\\s`]+))')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) {\n                $fileLine = if ($fileInference.Groups[2].Value) { $fileInference.Groups[2].Value } else { $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] $fileLine\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        $isNewFile = ($oldLine.Trim() -eq \"(new file)\")\n        $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$(if($isNewFile) { '[NEW_FILE]' } else { $oldLine })`n---`n$newText\"\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old='$oldLine' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n$obsMatch    = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n$observation = if ($obsMatch.Success) { $obsMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n$appliedInfo\n$(if($rejectedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Rejected: \" + ($rejectedMutations -join '; ') } else { \"\" })\n\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: $((Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure).Count)\n- Completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update pulse history\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$entry    = \"- $timestamp`: $observation$(if($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \" [applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')]\" })\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$updated  = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$entry\"\n$updated  | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - $observation\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382060399}}
{"type":"message","id":"30c4ea71","parentId":"f9c9fa46","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:54:29.826Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse script ran successfully but the output from the exec call was actually the content of the log file `pulse_2026-03-24 154814.md`. The script seems to have completed in the background with the output being the log file. But the timestamp is 154814 (3:48 PM), not 3:53 PM. That means the pulse that ran was from the 3:40 cron trigger, and the 3:50 cron trigger hasn't produced a newer log yet (or the new one is still being written).\n\nActually wait - looking at the exec output more carefully, the content from the log file was shown, ending with \"Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:48:36\". \n\nSo I'm seeing the log file from 15:48 being displayed. The current time is 15:53, which means the pulse should have triggered around 15:50. But the most recent file still shows 15:48 - either the new pulse is still running, or it failed to write a new file. Let me look more closely at that timestamp though, because there's something odd about it. I'm realizing the exec output was actually the contents of the 15:48 log file, not a new pulse run. The 15:53 cron trigger either hasn't completed yet or there's a delay in the log being written, so I need to check the system event log to see what's actually happening.","thinkingSignature":"3987d3821c434bb3ac1b65b1c38d513a6fffeb4346345ca7d03abbe54ec6af63"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cqzv6e04ejmg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 | Get-Content -Raw","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7217,"output":372,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19834,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774382060401}}
{"type":"message","id":"8926a4ea","parentId":"30c4ea71","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:54:30.413Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cqzv6e04ejmg_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 155352\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's been a major finding about CFI compression - CFI gives +32.9% precision but loses 92.9% recall\r\n3. The NEW INSIGHT is the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts, not causal information\r\n4. The key next step is the Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clear:\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq�160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe last pulse was pulse_2026-03-24 154814.md and \"No mutations applied this cycle.\"\r\n\r\nGiven Breakaway is a stateless discontinuous agent and needs to advance goals, I should implement the Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment. This is the most concrete next step based on the insights from the session.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Create a script or run the experiment to test the formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n2. Compare this against binary thresholds (CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120))\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist to understand the data structure. The CFI compression synthesis is in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`.\r\n\r\nI should create a script that:\r\n1. Loads the token data from previous pulses\r\n\r\n\r\n2. Applies the hybrid scoring formula to evaluate its effectiveness in distinguishing meaningful tokens from metaprogramming artifacts. This approach will help validate whether the new scoring method better captures the nuanced differences between constant format and research trajectory tokens.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified the \"Constant Format Problem\" and proposed a hybrid scoring formula, but this experiment hasn't been run yet. The next concrete step is implementing and testing Strategy C against the existing binary thresholds.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment script that implements score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) and runs a comparative analysis against binary thresholds on the 200-pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```python\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment\r\n# Tests Strategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# \r\n# Hypothesis: This formula should:\r\n#   - Suppress constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0  score=1.0x1.0=1.0... wait, that's still high)\r\n#   - Actually: freq/120 caps at 1.0, so const=160 gives min(1,1.33)=1.0\r\n#   - Need to reconsider: maybe use sqrt(freq) or log to dampen high frequencies\r\n#\r\n# Let me test: score(T) = CFI(T) x sqrt(min(freq, 160)) / sqrt(120)\r\n#   - Constant (freq=160): 1.0 x 12.65/10.95 = 1.16 (still high!)\r\n#   - Research trajectory (freq=100, CFI=0.8): 0.8 x 10/10.95 = 0.73\r\n#\r\n# Revised formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x (freq / 160)\r\n#   - Constant (freq=160, CFI=1.0): 1.0 x 1.0 = 1.0\r\n#   - Research (freq=100, CFI=0.8): 0.8 x 0.625 = 0.5\r\n#   - Research (freq=50, CFI=0.6): 0.6 x 0.3125 = 0.1875\r\n#\r\n# This better! But we need a threshold. Let's test score � 0.3\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data\r\ndef load_pulses(n=200):\r\n    # This is a placeholder - will load actual pulse tokens\r\n    pass\r\n\r\ndef compute_cfi_freq_scores(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute CFI 